  <h2>Demand Charges: ₹750/kVA/month</h2>

  <p>
    Maharashtra's demand charge is the highest in India at ₹750/kVA/month. Billing demand is the higher of:
  </p>

  <ol>
    <li>Actual Recorded Maximum Demand (MD) in kVA</li>
    <li>75% of the Contract Demand</li>
    <li>50 kVA minimum</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="warning-box">
    <strong>Capacity Utilization Warning:</strong> Industries with utilization below 75% pay a penalty on
    unutilized capacity. Ensure your contracted demand is right-sized. At ₹750/kVA, every 100 kVA of
    over-provisioning costs ₹75,000/month.
  </div>

